{
  "text": "At the time of writing, the genus comprised 46 species with validated names (www.bacterio.net/ [CITATION_1] ). Several species were isolated from plants, including Mucilaginibacter daejeonensis isolated from dried rice straw [CITATION_2] , Mucilaginibacter jinjuensis and Mucilaginibacter gynuensis isolated from rotten wood [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , Mucilaginibacter lappiensis isolated from lichen [CITATION_5] , Mucilaginibacter pineti isolated from pine wood [CITATION_6] , Mucilaginibacter polytrichastri isolated from moss [CITATION_7] , Mucilaginibacter vulcanisilvae isolated from volcanic forest [CITATION_8] , Mucilaginibacter auburnensis isolated from internal tissue of healthy corn stem [CITATION_9] and Mucilaginibacter polysacchareus isolated from the rhizoplane of the herb Angelica sinensis [CITATION_10] . Recently we proposed Mucilaginibacter phyllosphaerae, which was isolated from the phyllosphere of the herbaceous plant Galium album of the same environmental research station in Linden-Leihgestern near Giessen, Germany, as the strain described here [CITATION_11] .",
  "correct_citation": {
